{"TopicId":152146,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Cloud/Realistic atmosphere mod?","CreatedByName":"Kerbal the Kerbal","CreatedById":171262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-16T22:50:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal the Kerbal","CreatedById":171262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-16T22:50:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi. you found another question from me. Yay.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love the look of Kerbal Space Program, but I think i\u00A0do more. Is there any mod that i am able to\u00A0install\u00A0that is OPENGL compatible, which gives a much more smooth look to the atmospheres\u00A0to Eve, Duna, Kerbin, Jool, and possibly Laythe?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-17T01:30:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might want to try out SVE. It probably has what you want.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/143288-121-113-stock-visual-enhancements-114-1083/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal the Kerbal","CreatedById":171262,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-23T02:27:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk!\u00A0The \u0022Plernerts\u0022 (as i call them) look much more realistic now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the help!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sol Invictus","CreatedById":165953,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-26T14:14:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/143288-121-113-stock-visual-enhancements-114-1083/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ESVE\u003C/a\u003E improves only the visual aspect of the atmosphere. If you want your atmosphere to be realistic also in terms of the correct aerodynamics and pressures, you should look at \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/19321-113-ferram-aerospace-research-v01572-lanchester-7116/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E (sadly not yet updated for KSP 1.2.x) and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/128858-121-realistic-atmospheres/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ERealistic Atmospheres\u003C/a\u003E. Those two mods work awesomely in conjunction with each other, but you can also try them separately if you want. By the way, if SVE is too memory heavy for your PC, try plain \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/WazWaz/EnvironmentalVisualEnhancements/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E. Personally I like it more than SVE. Ah, and don\u0027t forget about installing \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/103963-wip12-scatterer-atmospheric-scattering-v00256-17102016/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Escatterer\u003C/a\u003E first, since neither SVE nor \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Environmental Visual Enhancement (mod)\u0022\u003EEVE\u003C/abbr\u003E will work to it\u0027s full potential without it. Speaking of visual improvements, there\u0027s also \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/130576-121-realplume-stock-configs-continued-v0111-20112016/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EReal Plume\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/87012-12-planetshine-v0252-stable-v05-experimental-4-october-2016/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EPlanet Shine\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/89214-12x-distant-object-enhancement-bis-v181-20-october-2016/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EDistant Object Enhancement\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/138919-12-galileos-sun-flares-v16/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EGalileo Sun Flares\u003C/a\u003E for you to consider. Only with all of those installed your atmospheric experience will be truly magnificent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-11-26T21:54:14Z\u0022 title=\u002211/26/2016 09:54  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Sol Invictus\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}